<h3>
  <span>3. Blocks scenarios:</span>
</h3>
<h3>Export Compliance Block: </h3>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="c6d8b271-4377-48a2-8f39-95c800ea826b">
    <strong>How to Check Export Compliance on Account</strong>: Click on the Account name in the contact details &gt; Account Page opens in New Sub tab &gt; Go to Details section &gt; See the Compliance information &gt; Observe the “Export Compliance Block” Checkbox. </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="250">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_10-52-45-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="39ec5ca8-f8c1-4b4c-b48d-da56e13710ec">
    <span>We are checking ECB Block at only for the Sold to CMF level Account. </span>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="13e86da9-58c7-471e-926d-d5260e6353d1">
    <span>In case creation, If the ECB block available then on click of New R4C create button it will display an error message &amp; not able to create case. It is an hard stop.</span>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="c6ff4fc2-914c-49ad-b417-c37d3455dd59">
    <span>In case Edit, If the ECB block available then on click of Edit button, then it will display an error message &amp; not able to Edit the case.</span>
  </li>
</ul>
<h3>Sold to Block (SAP Blocks): </h3>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="6729a86d-fa2a-4edb-bd02-3d4e31b7e72d">From account record page, go to ‘Related’ tab and there we can see ‘Customer BAG Account Associations’.  Open the related ‘Business Account Group’ (BAG) record. </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="250">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_10-52-59-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="e6d345d8-0241-4339-af30-51f6b14b0990">The related ‘BAG’ record open in a new subtab. Open ‘Related’ tab and we can see the ‘Customer CMFs’ associated with the Account in ‘Customer BAG CMF Associations’ </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="250">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_10-53-20-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="d235a275-75b7-43ab-be26-4c424de143b3">Click on any “Customer CMF” to open the corresponding record detail page. Navigate to ‘related’ tab and there we can see ‘Customer Partners (Partner CMF)’ records and their corresponding role code. </li>
  <li data-uuid="5925b472-5019-4623-85d9-3308bfe66444">If the ‘Customer CMF’ record has a related ‘Customer Partner’ record with role code “AG”, then that customer CMF record is eligible as a ‘sold to’ CMF. </li>
  <li data-uuid="a9e8208a-41e5-4705-bbfc-baba4bb42d97">This means that we have a valid sold to record for creating an R4C case. </li>
  <li data-uuid="e942bc03-6fbd-4474-b6dd-4cd57d1b0d89">All ‘Customer CMF’ records which have a related ‘Customer Partner’ record (with role code : AG) can be selected as sold to . </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="250">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_10-54-30-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="eef701d6-112c-4426-ba0a-cc4794f8a783">SAP blocks which are <strong>Central Order Block</strong>, <strong>Central Billing Block </strong>&amp; <strong>Central Delivery Block</strong>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <strong>
    <ac:image ac:height="250">
      <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_10-55-20-1.png"/>
    </ac:image>
  </strong>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="4b86fd80-de61-428f-8c3c-9d603b9ad096">Check if there is any <span>Central Order Block, Central Billing Block &amp; Central Delivery Block. Otherwise, directly check the blocks at Sales Area Level. (No need to check other blocks at CMF level) </span>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="c6e2e6f6-509e-454d-9fc2-d6445ce6aa98">If <strong>central order block</strong> is present i.e., (Customer Central Order Block = <strong>‘01’ or ‘02’ or ‘03’ or ‘99</strong>’) it is a hard stop and an error toast message will be displayed with the corresponding blocks information. </li>
  <li data-uuid="e530fa94-1351-4d53-bab8-68f23bb7786f">If <strong>central billing block</strong> is present and billing block value (Customer Central Billing Block=<strong>”99” or “12”</strong>) then it is a hard stop, and an error toast message will be displayed with the corresponding blocks information. </li>
  <li data-uuid="86cb22d8-f72b-4a0a-b971-62448cb1b9e4">
    <span>If <strong>Central Delivery block</strong> is present and Delivery block value (Central Delivery block = “<strong>99</strong>”) then it is a hard stop and an error toast message will be displayed with the corresponding blocks information. </span>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <span>
    <strong>Note:</strong>
  </span>
  <span> </span>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="7e93a586-26c2-4045-aef4-9947159948c9">
    <span>In Case Edit, If any of the SAP Block is available at Sold to CMF level then on click of Case Edit button, it will display an error toast message &amp; not able to Edit the case.</span>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="c65d683f-54ab-4a15-b3f3-dc9409769be4">
    <span>In Case Edit, If any of the SAP Block is available at Sold to CMF level then on click of Case Edit button, it will display an error toast message &amp; not able to Edit the case.</span>
    <span>In Case creation, If any of the SAP Block is available at Sold to CMF level then that Sold To CMF will not be displayed in the Sold To selection.</span>
  </li>
</ul>
<h3>Sold To Sales Area Blocks (SAP Blocks): </h3>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="9cd24ebe-ee9a-48a7-95f4-1c5a304d4e30">Based on the selected sold to CMF, we will fetch the corresponding sales area records which are related to sold to ‘Customer CMF’ record. </li>
  <li data-uuid="668fb998-9f66-4735-a2be-2102870b0675">To view the corresponding sales area records: </li>
  <li data-uuid="7289bb09-6db1-4b09-9dd7-0c73d99ead89">Open the sold to Customer CMF record and navigate to related tab.</li>
  <li data-uuid="295d88fa-6fd1-4647-9055-0f7f9e73e0fc">There we can see all the related ‘Customer Sales Area’ records. </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="250">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_10-57-56-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<p>
  <br/>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="ac2a9745-d3e3-476f-bccb-3336ec7937c5">At the sales area level we can have similar SAP blocks like that of sold to (CMF level): <ul>
      <li data-uuid="caee2374-cc1f-4bd8-9bff-93f82a2b62d2">Order block </li>
      <li data-uuid="9fa20ccd-e722-4a5b-a394-60835f66a8d2">
        <span>Billing block</span>
      </li>
      <li data-uuid="b297cc33-73de-429d-8365-b67ed2b10ac0">
        <span>Delivery block</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="ff4f8eec-296f-4a79-bc17-124b67902daf">To check the blocks at the Sales Area level, Go to CMF &gt; Click on “Related “tab &gt; Click on “Customer Sales Area” &gt; open the Sales area and select the record &gt; Open and see the Block Values </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="250">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_10-58-16-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="620028c6-9c08-40dc-8bc7-8a895e9e1bdb">
    <span>Check if there is any Order Block, Billing Block &amp; Delivery Block at Sold To Sales Area level. </span>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="a39e8722-29e5-43f7-a0b2-5bf83a54bf73">
    <span>If <strong>order block</strong> is present i.e., (Order Block = <strong>‘01’ or ‘02’ or ‘03’ or ‘99</strong>’) it is a hard stop and an error toast message will be displayed with the corresponding blocks information. </span>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="f428eb69-ccdd-486c-945b-3b94d7294918">
    <span>If <strong>billing block</strong> is present and billing block value (Billing Block=<strong>”99” or “12”</strong>) then it is a hard stop, and an error toast message will be displayed with the corresponding blocks information. </span>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="3f83b432-06ec-4e95-b89d-9384fc39338b">
    <span>If <strong>Delivery block</strong> is present and Delivery block value (Delivery block = “<strong>99</strong>”) then it is a hard stop and an error toast message will be displayed with the corresponding blocks information. </span>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="cc473fc7-78b5-4b30-948f-e0012dfca0c9">
    <span>
      <strong>Note:</strong>
    </span>
    <span> </span>
    <ul>
      <li data-uuid="76cd8aae-d5ea-44b3-b0aa-ea7312486aa5">
        <span>In Case creation, If any of the above SAP Block is available at Sold to Sales Area level then that Sales Area will not be displayed in the Sales Area selection.</span>
      </li>
      <li data-uuid="2e07f122-17ae-4b2f-ba73-3190c72165fc">
        <span>In Case Edit, If any of the above SAP Block is available at Sold to Sales Area level then on click of Case Edit button, it will display an error toast message &amp; not able to Edit the case.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<h3>Payer CMF Blocks: </h3>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="c4d9cc86-9266-481e-8f14-c930c646fa24">Based on the selected Sold to and Sales area value, we will fetch Payer record from Customer partner record with role code ‘RG’. </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="250">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_10-58-36-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="35d467bb-1086-4d75-bca9-9546152a0973">If no Payer record is found then it will be hard stop and  Agent/Portal user will be notified in case of hard stop by error toast message. </li>
  <li data-uuid="c5c93ed1-a736-4ac7-8216-a53e9b107ee8">If there is at least one Active Payer for the selected Sold To and Sales area combination, then we get the CMF and Sales area record related to Payer record and check for SAP blocks as mentioned below. </li>
  <li data-uuid="23636915-10db-447e-bb88-0a45384b5cc1">Payer Order block &amp; billing block</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="250">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_10-58-53-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="2026dae0-2486-4d35-9188-25ba5ea1d98d">If Central order block = “02” then it is a hard stop and an error message will be displayed with the corresponding blocks information.</li>
  <li data-uuid="c5f1e510-64d3-439b-ab37-d83ff642a3b1">If Central Billing Block = ‘08’ or ‘12’ or ‘99’, then it is a hard stop, and an error toast message will be displayed with the corresponding blocks information. </li>
</ul>
<p>
  <span>
    <strong>Note:</strong>
  </span>
  <span> </span>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="eb7d55a4-16ad-4bae-bbb3-326ce1423ad1">
    <span>In Case creation, If any of the above SAP Block is available at Payer CMF level then on selection of the related Sold To it will display an error toast message.</span>
  </li>
