<h3>7. Product Validation:</h3>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="150">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-20-55-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="f7a87ef2-b908-402f-8a57-5fed182da1aa">If the Product Status is “35, 45, 75, 65, 25, 55”, it will pass the product validation step , if the status is not out of these then the line item is disabled. (Hard Stop)</li>
  <li data-uuid="68663e9f-b960-48f1-8809-15d3e9c0b233">if the Product status is <strong>15 </strong>and <strong>05 </strong>the line item is disabled. (Hard Stop) with a error message saying “current status is 15 (Pre-Active)” / “current status is 05 (Not Implemented)”</li>
  <li data-uuid="e7e3e0b0-67b4-4923-9e29-ed5cb640efea">If the Product status is “45 (End of Life)”, then “Get Last Order Entry Date, PCN date and Last Return Dates from MDG”.<ul>
      <li>If “LOE and PCN date” are not available, then disable the line item (Hard Stop)</li>
      <li>If “LOE and PCN date” available, then check “Last Order date is &gt;= 4 months since PCN/PDN publish date”.<ul>
          <li>If yes, then “LOE Date= what is in PCN”</li>
          <li>If no, then “last order date by taking PCN/PDN publish date + 120 days”</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Check if Last Return date available.<ul>
          <li>If available, then check “Current date is within Last Return date?”. If not matches, then hard stop.</li>
          <li>If not available, then “Last Return Date = Last Order Entry date + 30 days” and see if it is matching “Current date is within Last Return date?”. If matches proceed with checking for Spec code.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>If the Product status is “35 (Active)”, then directly check for Spec Codes.<ul>
          <li>If the Spec Code is either of these “Q”, then the line item is disabled (Hard Stop)</li>
          <li>If the Spec Code is not from any of the above, then proceed further.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>If the MM is “CTO” /” HPC” then it is Hard Stop.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="ee8a5a2f-bdd3-472d-a4e3-29a96b57e7ca">Validating allowance record for each line item as follows<ul>
      <li data-uuid="7171fa52-d22e-499a-8486-07215b39fa22">Based on product/OPID of each line item</li>
