<ul>
  <li data-uuid="c5ac17d2-621c-4863-b336-65077a7e1bab">
    <span>When user clicks on ‘Save &amp; View Summary’ or ‘Save for Later’, additional validation called as ‘CPN Indicator check’ is done. For the selected Sold To CMF, the value of ‘Is CPN required?’ field is fetched.</span>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="38cd41ff-8870-4512-be9f-cb92653b5c43">
    <span>If the field value is ‘True’, then all the line items are validated for CPN values.</span>
  </li>
  <li data-uuid="1b7442ee-9346-4c28-8fa4-5e169b0e2a2f">
    <span>Any line item that doesn’t have CPN value is disabled and shown to agent. The corresponding error message can be seen in the validation column for the disabled line items.</span>
  </li>
</ul>
<h3>
  <span>
    <strong>15. Export to CSV:</strong>
  </span>
  <span>
    <strong> </strong>
  </span>
</h3>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="910aba00-f932-4eb4-8531-4cd8ce958a6f">In the ‘Case details and description’ section where we add and validate the line items, customer has the option to export all the line items present in that particular stage.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="250">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-38-40-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="9ec00aa7-6bb3-42b0-b857-73026f272b19">When customer clicks on ‘Export to CSV’, all the line-items present on the screen will be formatted into CSV, which would then be downloaded automatically.</li>
  <li data-uuid="40b9d54d-f422-47c9-93db-73edc703a525">For ‘Stock Rotation’, customer will be able to the see the button in ‘Product validation’, ‘Credit price validation’ and ‘Allowance matrix validation’ stages.</li>
  <li data-uuid="d05d0d09-df3f-4502-bcca-0b1ba593c511">Customer is allowed to export before and after the validation on that particular stage. The downloaded file will display the corresponding success and error messages for line items after validation.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="150">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-38-54-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="4f97e8f3-b77d-45f2-aa26-93e402a093a9">All the details which customer is able to see on the UI will be available in the downloaded sheet including details shown in ‘More info’ icon.</li>
</ul>
<h3>
  <strong>16. Duplicate MM:</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
  <li data-uuid="bd10dfe6-b532-4b01-9cea-4c481bd179df">Agent has the option to create additional line items using any previously used MM number.</li>
  <li data-uuid="deb3ea76-67a1-49cd-95cf-8298a85f2adf">Agent can do multiple searches and re trigger the same search multiple times using same set of data.</li>
  <li data-uuid="96c99151-8711-4420-beff-1efaf7fdd700">He should be able to search with the same MM and allow to add multiple line items for the same MM.</li>
  <li data-uuid="ae2a6d5f-e0f3-4e30-b287-b76c05cfab0e">To make this functionality feasible, Invoice Number is used in to calculate uniqueness, it is a unique number created for each line item.</li>
  <li data-uuid="5265d0a1-fb69-494a-95bb-011f1b318eae">We will add 6-digit random number at start of invoice number that will make it unique even if duplicate MMs are received.</li>
</ul>
<h3>
  <strong>17. SF &lt;-&gt; </strong>
  <strong>S/4</strong>
</h3>
<p>Once the case is submitted in salesforce and the status is “RMA Authorized”. The case is sent to S/4 via MULE middleware system every 15mins by Auto-sys job.</p>
<p>After 15 mins, the outbound job is run by ECC and the Delivery Note number, Case line status, Order MSGV1 &amp; Order MSGV2 are updated.</p>
<p>If there are any errors, GTS blocks received from S4 then the Case details will have the consolidated error messages for each line item, like displayed in below Screenshot.</p>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="250">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-39-49-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<p>Once the Shipment order is created in S/4 side, the Bill of lading Number is sent to Salesforce. The shipment tracking information will be shown under shipment tracking tab.</p>
<p>Open the Shipment tracking tab opens can see all the line items. Line items that has the Status as “IN Transit”/ “Delivered” will have the link to go the shipment information.</p>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="250">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-40-18-1.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
<p>
  <br/>
</p>
<p>Click on the “In Transit” link and see the Shipment and tracking details information opening. All the events that are occurred will be displayed in the table.</p>
<p>
  <ac:image ac:height="250">
    <ri:attachment ri:filename="image-2026-7-6_11-40-52.png"/>
  </ac:image>
</p>
